{
  "texts": [
    "They propose formal mechanisms-such as prioritization rules and conflict resolution protocols-to ensure cooperative behavior in multi-agent systems.",
    "Their work demonstrates that constraints can be algorithmically embedded to guide autonomous agents toward socially optimal outcomes, akin to traffic rules for AI.",
    "Unlike Ostrom's human-centric models, these social laws are not negotiated but designed.",
    "In contrast to the spontaneously emerging norms of self-governing systems, they are predefined, codified, and embedded (also see Van de Poel, 2020, for a related discussion in the context of non-autonomous AI).",
    "Yet this approach raises its own challenges: In a landscape of competing AI developers and stakeholders, who defines these laws?"
  ]
}